articles.headline: Mason Greenwood on target as Marseille reach Coupe de France quarterfinals
articles.description: Marseille reached the quarter-finals of the Coupe de France with a 3-0 victory over Rennes at Stade Velodrome.

images.name: Mason Greenwood [1296x729]
images.caption: Mason Greenwood scored his 22nd goal of the season as Marseille saw off Rennes in the Coupe de France.
images.credit: Photo by MIGUEL MEDINA / AFP via Getty Images

articles.headline: Mason Greenwood hat trick leads 9-goal rout by Marseille
articles.description: Marseille's Mason Greenwood scored a hat trick in a 9-0 rout of sixth-tier Bayeux in the Coupe de France.

articles.headline: Paris Saint-Germain stunned in French Cup by neighbors Paris FC
articles.description: Jonathan Ikoné returned to haunt his former club as Paris FC claimed an historic 1-0 win over neighbours Paris Saint-Germain in the round of 32 of the Coupe de France.

articles.headline: PSG start Coupe de France defence with simple win
articles.description: Paris Saint-Germain started their Coupe de France defence with a 4-0 win at fifth-tier Vendée Fontenay to reach the last 32 on Saturday.

articles.headline: Soccer's longest away trips: Truro's got nothing on the 'Distance Derby'
articles.description: As Truro prepare to make the longest round trip for a professional league match in English football history, here's a look at the furthest that teams have to travel every season.

articles.headline: PSG treble hopes alive after French Cup final rout of Reims
articles.description: Holders Paris Saint-Germain cruised to a 3-0 victory over Stade de Reims in the Coupe de France final on Saturday, claiming a third domestic trophy for the second successive season, and preparing for next week's Champions League final in style.
